<CITE><U>Combating Violent Crime,</U></CITE> pp. 1618; Cary, &quot;How  States
Can Fight Violent Crime,&quot; pp. 1011; J.  Markman and Paul G. Cassell, &quot;Protecting
the  Innocent: A Response to the BedavRadelet Study,&quot; 
<CITE><U>Stanford Law Review</U></CITE>, Vol. 41 (1988), pp. 121,  154156; 
<!-- Generation of PM publication page 12 -->  Stephen K. Layson, &quot;Homicide
and Deterrence:  A Reexamination of the United States Times Series Evidence,&quot;

<CITE><U>Southern Economics Journal</U></CITE>, Vol. 52, pp. 68, 7580.
Legislation  providing for the death penalty for these crimes  should be adopted
in every state and at the  federal level.
</P>
<P><TT><B><A NAME="82">82</A></B></TT> For other
helpful reforms, see U.S.  Department of Justice, <CITE><U>Combating Violent 
