<HEAD>
<TITLE>Myers, Continued</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<CENTER><H2>Myers, Continued</H2></CENTER>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<P>
MediaNomics noted recently that NBC's Lisa Myers has been emerging as one of 
the most original network reporters. During July, the trend continued.
<P>
Last month Myers reported again on sugar subsidies for Dateline. She pointed 
out that the program costs consumers while a limited number of sugar growers 
get billions in subsidies.
<P>
Then, in a Nightly News story, she returned to the Medicare debate. Myers 
reported again that most recipients receive much more in benefits than they 
paid into the program and that Medicare's explosive growth wasn't predicted by 
its founders.
<P>
Myers' fact-based reporting continues to clear up the often foggy enntitlements 
debate.
<P>
<DD> 
<P>
<P>
<P>
<DD> 
<P>
<DD> 
<P>
<P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BODY>
</HTML>
