<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE></TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY background="li-paper.gif" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#0000FF" ALINK="#0000FF">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="li-logo.gif"></CENTER>

</P>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B><STRONG><BIG><CENTER>The 25th Annual Conservative Fourth of July Soiree</CENTER></BIG></STRONG></B></FONT>

 </P>Hundreds of conservative activists.  Whole roast pigs.  Family activities. Ideal location</P>               

</P>That’s the 25th Annual Fourth of July Soiree.</P>								</P>And I invite you to attend.</P>			
</P>Can you think of a better way to celebrate the Fourth of July?  I’d be honored if you and your family would
come and join me at the Fourth of July Soiree.  It’s an ideal opportunity for you, your family, friends and colleagues to celebrate the values and principles upon which this country was founded.  Let’s keep this fine conservative tradition going by celebrating together the birth of our nation.</P>
					</P>The shelter at Fort Hunt Park has already been reserved for this year’s Soiree.  Fort Hunt is located on the George Washington Parkway near Mt.Vernon.  It’s a convenient location for everyone.</P>
						</P>Read a list of <A HREF="sponsors.htm"> recent patrons and sponsors</A>.  There’s also a convenient<A HREF="direct.htm"> directions</A> for finding the park.  Feel free to tell your conservative friends about the Soiree and to visit our internet site at <A HREF="http://lead-inst.org">http://www.lead-inst.org</A></P>
								</P>The Soiree is  a uniquley patriotic occassion you and your entire family will remember for years.  For those who want to spread out and enjoy  the company of other conservatives, there is lots of space available at the park.  There are also two volleyball courts and a softball field.</P>

</P>This year we’ll hold a conservative olympics for teams of five to participate in.  So assemble your team today.
There will be a number of activities for the kids again this year.  Ross the Clown was a big hit last year, 
and we’ll try to have him back again.</P>

</P>The very popular Roast Pig, or rather a close descendent, will again be on the menu this year. Last year’s crowd of 
five hundred people dispatched three large hogs.  The Soiree is a cooperative gathering of conservatives.</P>

</P>The heart of the program will feature an old-fashioned political stump speech.  Speeches are seldom considered entetainment in this town, but the Soiree is known for its verbal fireworks.  It’s free, fun, patriotic.  And only once a year.</P>

</P>Please join me in celebrating the Fourth of July at the 25th Annual Conservative Soiree.</P>

</P>Cordially,</P>
<IMG SRC="/lead-inst/mortsig.gif">

</P>Morton C. Blackwell</P>
</P>President, The Leadership Institute</P>

<B><U><U></P>P.S. Please feel  free to eMail me anytime by clicking here: <a href="mailto:lead@townhall.com">lead@townhall.com</a> </P></U></U></B>
</P>
</P>
