<li>7/19/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/bg1086.html">The Historical Lessons of Lower Tax Rates</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/mitchell.htm">Daniel J. Mitchell</a>. (Backgrounder #1086)





<li>7/1/96 <a href="/heritage/p_review/jul96/bless.html">How Business Delivers the Good</a> by John Hood. (July-August Policy Review: The Journal of American Citizenship)



<li>5/17/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/theory/fyi102.html">How To Raise Take-Home Pay Without Destroying Jobs</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/wilson.htm">Mark Wilson</a> and <a href="/heritage/staff/antonel.htm">Angela Antonelli</a>. (F.Y.I. #102) 

<li>5/14/96 <a href="http://www.townhall.com/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/lect565.html">Taxes, Deficits, and Economic Growth</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/mitchell.htm">Daniel J. Mitchell</a>. (Lecture No. 565)  


<li>5/1/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/bg1078.html">Is There a "Clinton Crunch"?: How the 1993 Budget Plan Affected the Economy</a> by Scott A. Hodge, William W. Beach, John S. Barry, Mark Wilson, and Joe Cobb. (Backgrounder #1078) 
<li>5/1/96 <a href="/heritage/p_review/may96/wepeo.html">Micro Wave</a> by <a hr
ef="/heritage/staff/meyerson.htm">Adam Meyerson</a>. (May-June 1996 Policy Review: The Journal of American Citizenship)
<li>4/22/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/theory/bgup275.html">The Folly of Increasing the Minimum Wage</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/wilson.htm">Mark Wilson</a>. (Backgrounder Update #275)
<li>4/19/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/theory/fyi97.html">Wages, Profits, and Income: Politics Vs. Reality</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/wilson.htm">Mark Wilson</a>. (F.Y.I. #97)
<li>4/19/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/theory/fyi96.html">Why Americans Are Right To Be Anxious In Clinton's Lackluster Economy</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/wilson.htm">Mark Wilson</a>. (F.Y.I. #96)
<li>4/8/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/trade/bg1077.html">The Myths and Realities of Trade Protectionism</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/johnson.htm">Bryan T. Johnson</a>. (Backgrounder #1077)
<li>2/27/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/lect556.html">Freeing America from the Clinton Crunch: A Congressional Agenda for Economic Growth</a> by The Honorable Dick Armey. (Heritage Lecture #556)
<li>12/12/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/theory/lect552.html">A Tale of Two Pesos: A Comparison of Currency Policies In Mexico and Argentina</a> by Steve H. Hanke. (Lecture #552)
<li>7/5/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/trade/bg1039.html">The Myths and Realities of Trade Deficits</a> by Bryan T. Johnson. (Backgrounder #1039)
<li>3/11/94 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/theory/bg982.html">Preparing for the "Jobs" Summit: The Five Principles of Job Creation</a> by Adam Thierer. (Backgrounder #982)


<li>10/23/91 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/bg862.htm
l">A Five-Plank Program for Trade and Investment with Eastern Europe and
the
Former Soviet Republics</a> by William D. Rogers. (Backgrounder #862)
</ul><p>
