<center><h2><font size=+3>T</font>he <font size=+3>H</font>eritage <font size=+3>F</font>oundation</h2></center>
<center><h3><font size=+2>P</font>ublications <font size=+2>L</font>ibrary</h3>
<hr size=3 width=50%>
<p>
<b>National Security: Missile Defense and Arms Control
</b>
</center>
<ul><p>
<b>Books:</b>
<p>
<a href="/heritage/congress/chapt7.html">How the 104th Congress Has Protected the Nation's Security</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/moore.html">Thomas Moore</a>. (<i>Reviewing the Revolution: Conservative Successes in the 104th Congress</i>)<p>
<b>Policy Papers:</b>
<p>
<li>1/17/97 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/em466.html">Why A Global Ban on Land Mines Won't Work</a> by <A HREF="/heritage/staff/spring.htm">Baker Spring</a> and <A HREF="/heritage/staff/hillen.html">John Hillen</a>. (Executive Memorandum #466) 
<li>9/12/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/em460.html">The Chemical Weapons Convention: Unverifiable, Unenforceable, and a Burden to Business</a>  by <a href="/heritage/staff/spring.htm">Baker Spring</a>. (Executive Memorandum #460) 

<li>7/18/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/fyi111.html">Ratifying the Chemical Weapons Convention: American Business Will Pay the Price</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/spring.htm">Baker Spring</a>. (F.Y.I. #111) 
<li>5/30/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/fyi106.html">The CBO Estimate On Missile Defense: A Case of Flaws and Distortions</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/spring.htm">Baker Spring</a>. (F.Y.I. #106) 


<li>5/21/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/fyi103.html">Flawed Intelligence Report No Guide To Missile Threat</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/spring.htm">Baker Spring</a>. (F.Y.I. #103)  
<li>4/15/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/cb25.html">The Chemical Weapons Convention: A Bad Deal for America</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/spring.htm">Baker Spring</a>. (Committee Brief #25)
<li>3/15/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/bg1074.html">Defending America: Ending America's Vulnerability to Ballistic Missiles</a> by the Missile Defense Study Team. (Backgrounder #1074)
<li>12/15/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/bgup266.html">Clinton Is Bypassing the Senate on the ABM Treaty</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/spring.htm">Baker Spring</a>. (Backgrounder Update #266, updating Backgrounder #867, "Removing the ABM Treaty Obstacle to U.S. and Soviet Defenses Against Missiles," November 15, 1991.)
<li>10/31/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/cb21.html">Conditions for Ratifying START II</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/spring.htm">Baker Spring</a>. (Committee Brief #21)
<li>9/21/95 <a href="http://www.townhall.com/heritage/library/categories/natsec/bg1054.html">The House-Senate Conference Should Agree To Rapid Deployment of Missile Defenses</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/spring.htm">Baker Spring</a>. (Backgrounder No. 1054)



<li>8/23/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/em427.html">Will America Remain a Nuclear Power? Implications of Clinton's Nuclear Test Ban</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/spring.htm">Baker Spring</a>. (Executive Memorandum #427) 
<li>8/1/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/em423.html">The Missile Defense Act of 1995: The Senate's Historic Opportunity</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/moore.html">Thomas Moore</a>. (Executive Memorandum #423)
<li>7/7/95 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/cbrief16.html">Clinton's ABM Treaty Muddle</a> by Kim Holmes and Baker Spring. (Committee Brief #16)
</ul><p>
